data.enText: to fasten sth or be fastened with a buckle
These shoes buckle at the side.
to become crushed or bent under a weight or force; to crush or bend sth in this way

data.chText: 钢架在重压下开始变形。
data.enText: The steel frames began to buckle under the strain.

data.chText: 意志薄弱的人在这种压力下可能就垮了。
data.enText: A weaker man would have buckled under the pressure.

data.chText: 我的汽车前部被撞扁了。
data.enText: The crash buckled the front of my car.
when your knees or legs buckle or when you buckle at the knees, your knees become weak and you start to fall
to start to do sth seriously

data.chText: 我最好认真静下来努力完成那些报告。
data.enText: I'd better buckle down to those reports.
a piece of metal or plastic used for joining the ends of a belt or for fastening a part of a bag, shoe, etc.

ex.enText: His face was distorted with pain.

ex.chText: 在什么情况下金属会变形？
ex.enText: In what condition will metal distort?

synonyms.bx: 指改变某物的外观、声音等使其变得怪异或模糊，也指某物发生此种变化。

ex.chText: 钢架在烈火的高温下开始变形。
ex.enText: The steel frame began to buckle under the intense heat of the fire.
The bumper was buckled by the crash.

synonyms.bx: 指某物因高温、压力等作用而变形。

ex.chText: 这种金属在压力下会变形。
ex.enText: This kind of metal will deform under pressure.

ex.chText: 长时间穿过紧的鞋会使双脚变形。
ex.enText: Wearing tight shoes for long time can deform your feet.

synonyms.bx: 指在外力作用下或外在环境影响下某物的外形发生变化，造成功能或外观受损。

ex.chText: 地板在潮湿的环境里会变得翘曲不平。
ex.enText: The floorboards will warp in a damp environment.

ex.chText: 如果门变形了，你最好买个新的来。
ex.enText: If the door is warped, you'd better buy a new one.

synonyms.bx: 指形状在温度、湿度的作用下发生改变。

data.enText: to start to do sth seriously

data.chText: 我最好认真静下来努力完成那些报告。
data.enText: I'd better buckle down to those reports.

tr: fastener that fastens together two ends of a belt or strap
a shape distorted by twisting or folding
bend out of shape, as under pressure or from heat
example: The highway buckled during the heat wave

tr: fasten with a buckle or buckles

value.def: A buckle is a piece of metal or plastic attached to one end of a belt or strap, which is used to fasten it.

example.ex: He wore a belt with a large brass buckle.
example.tran: 他系了条带有一个大的铜搭扣的皮带。

value.def: When you buckle a belt or strap, you fasten it.

example.ex: A door slammed in the house and a man came out buckling his belt.
example.tran: 房子里的一扇门砰地关上，一个男子边扣腰带边走了出来。

value.def: If an object buckles or if something buckles it, it becomes bent as a result of very great heat or force.

example.ex: The door was beginning to buckle from the intense heat...
example.tran: 门在高温高热下开始变形。

example.ex: A freak wave had buckled the deck.
example.tran: 突然掀起的巨浪打弯了甲板。

value.tran: （因受热或受力）（使）弯曲，（使）变形

value.def: If your legs or knees buckle, they bend because they have become very weak or tired.

example.ex: Mcanally's knees buckled and he crumpled down onto the floor...
example.tran: 麦卡纳利双膝发软，瘫倒在地板上。

example.ex: His right leg buckled under him.

value.tran: （双腿或膝盖因虚弱、劳累）发软
